  "texts": [
    "Monitoring Barriers No transparency requirements or oversight mechanisms exist for demotion of legal content, granting unchecked power to dominant platforms over online discourse flows (Article 27 & Recital 56).",
    "5Expanded reporting and auditing enhance accountability but standardization gaps and data access limits may constrain holistic monitoring by authorities and researchers (Articles 13, 28, 35) [107,183].",
    "In particular for auditing, audit findings may inform future regulatory interventions or enforcement actions if systemic non-compliance is uncovered (Code: AD).",
    "Nevertheless, audits are limited to assessing procedural compliance rather than evaluating substantive fairness, proportionality or effectiveness (Recital 92), also in regards to AI systems deployed [28].",
    "As remarked before, the level of genuine independence between powerful platforms and auditors remains unclear (Article 37).Shadow Banning Connected to transparency regulation in content moderation, the DSA is the first to address the issue of shadow banning directly."
  ],
